{"id":682,"date":"2008-08-13T07:59:27","date_gmt":"2008-08-13T12:59:27","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/in_brief_will_the_real_bruce_p.php"},"modified":"2008-08-13T07:59:27","modified_gmt":"2008-08-13T12:59:27","slug":"in_brief_will_the_real_bruce_p","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/in_brief_will_the_real_bruce_p.php","title":{"rendered":"In Brief: Will the Real Bruce Please Stand Up?"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/inbrief_akzonobel.gif\" alt=\"Akzo Nobel Sketches\" \/><\/p>\n<div class=\"in_brief\">Three months ago <a href=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/reach_out_and_touch_me.php\">we reported on the rebranding of AkzoNobel<\/a>, noting that Saffron had designed the logo but not mentioning that <a href=\"http:\/\/blog.pentagram.com\/2008\/06\/new-work-akzo-nobel.php\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Pentagram (London) had later implemented the identity<\/a>, I assume I wasn&#8217;t aware of this at the time, which brings us to the matter at hand&hellip; Martijn Rijven, an Amsterdam-based illustrator and designer, was responsible for drawing Bruce (as the pointing man is referred to in the inner circle) and <a href=\"http:\/\/boltgraphics.blogspot.com\/2008\/08\/bruce-me.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">has written an extensive post about the process<\/a>, with a great video at the bottom, showing the evolution of the drawing and mourning the truncated version of his drawing that was the final logo &mdash; or as Rijven describes it, &#8220;they appear to have sank him into the ground and left him begging an invisible passer by to take his aged skinny hand to drag him out.&#8221;<\/div>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/images\/excerpt_empty.gif\" alt=\"Excerpt Em